[thinking] **Exploring constructors and setters**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering the importance of discovering setters after creating a constructor. It seems like constructors initialize an object's state, while setters are used later to modify that state. It’s interesting how they work together—constructor sets the initial values, and setters allow for flexibility. I wonder how often people overlook the benefit of having effective setters as they design their classes. This could really enhance code maintainability!
